{"id":7831,"date":"2018-06-23T12:01:12","date_gmt":"2018-06-23T11:01:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/?p=7831"},"modified":"2021-12-16T17:56:05","modified_gmt":"2021-12-16T16:56:05","slug":"hot-springs-iceland","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/iceland\/hot-springs-iceland\/","title":{"rendered":"6 Best Hot Springs in Iceland"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-1-hrunalaug-one-of-the-hot-springs-in-iceland\">1. Hrunalaug &#x2013; One of the hot springs in Iceland<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The most picturesque and secret natural hot pool is Hrunalaug. With just 1,5-hour from <a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/iceland\/things-to-do-reykjavik\/\">Reykjavik<\/a>, this tiny changing room is hidden in between the mountains behind a small village. The hot spring can host up to 15 people and usually isn&#x2019;t crowded. On the weekends, some locals will have a beer here as well. There is a fee box, please leave the amount requested on the box. Hrunalaug belongs to the <a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/iceland\/things-must-do-iceland\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">things you must do in Iceland<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153447\/hot-springs-iceland-Hrunalaug-house.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img width=\"261\" height=\"338\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"7928\" class=\"wp-image-7928 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1484px) 100vw, 1484px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153447\/hot-springs-iceland-Hrunalaug-house.jpg 1484w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153447\/hot-spr