called the oldest swimming pool of Iceland. It is quite hidden from the main road and it takes a 15-minute hike down the valley to get here. It&#x2019;s located in between Seljalandsfoss and Skogafoss. The pool is maintained through donations so please leave a small gift behind.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--mustread \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--mustread\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Must Read: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/iceland\/camping-iceland\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Iceland camping guide<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n<div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153254\/30078515_436321600142415_7555113362204393472_n-810x810.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img class=\"alignnone size-large lazypreload\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153254\/30078515_436321600142415_7555113362204393472_n-600x600.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153254\/30078515_436321600142415_7555113362204393472_n-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153254\/30078515_436321600142415_7555113362204393472_n-100x100.jpg 100w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23153254\/30078515_436321600142415_7555113362204393472_n-338x338.jpg 338w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23